                           CAFE BLISS DOCUMENTATION

Project: Café Bliss – Café Website
Author: Joy Kendi Mwongera
Date: 2025
Website Purpose: Showcase Café Bliss, provide menu information, and allow customers to contact the café.

1. Overview

The Café Bliss website is a multi-page responsive website designed to provide a modern, elegant, and user-friendly interface for café visitors. The website includes:
Home Page: Hero section with welcome message, image, and CTA button
About Page: Information about the café, images, and typing text effect
Menu Page: Display of café menu items (future implementation can include dynamic menu)
Contact Page: Contact information and a functional contact form

The design emphasizes coffee-inspired colors, a navy blue background, and a subtle watermark across pages to reinforce branding.

2. Technology Stack

Component	Description
HTML5	Structure of web pages
CSS3	Styling, layout, and responsive design
JavaScript	Mobile menu toggle and typing text effect
Images	Hero, About, and contact images for visual appeal

3.File Structure

CafeBliss/
│
├── index.html          # Home Page
├── about.html          # About Page
├── menu.html           # Menu Page
├── contact.html        # Contact Page
│
├── css/
│   └── style.css       # Common styling for all pages
│
├── js/
│   └── main.js         # JavaScript functionality (menu toggle)
│
└── images/
    ├── hero.jpg
    ├── about.jpg
    └── cafe-front.jpg

4. Pages and Features

4.1 Home Page (index.html)
Hero Section with welcome <h1> and description <p> centered above the image
Hero Image: showcases the café ambiance
CTA Button: “See Our Menu” directs users to the menu page
Responsive Header/Footer: Coffee-brown header, dark footer, navigation menu

4.2 About Page (about.html)
About Image showing inside the café
Typing Text Effect: Animated text introducing the café’s philosophy
Watermark: Large diagonal text “Café Bliss” as branding
Responsive design: Works on desktop and mobile

4.3 Menu Page (menu.html)
Placeholder for menu items (images, names, descriptions, prices)
Styled similarly to Home and About pages for consistent look

4.4 Contact Page (contact.html)
Contact Information: Phone and email
Contact Form: Name, Email, Message, and Submit button
Hero Image / Café Image for visual context
Responsive Header/Footer and watermark consistent with other pages

5. Styling & Design Choices

Primary Colors:
Coffee Brown: #6b4226 for headers
Navy Blue: #001f3f background
Buttons: Coral #ff7f50 with hover effect

Typography:
Font: Arial, sans-serif for readability
Header & Hero: Bold, clear

Watermark:
Subtle, diagonal “Café Bliss” across all pages
Fixed position with low opacity (0.07)

Responsiveness:
Flexbox used for header and layout
Mobile menu toggle with JavaScript

6. JavaScript Functionality
Mobile Menu Toggle:
const menuBtn = document.querySelector('.menu-toggle');
const nav = document.querySelector('nav');
menuBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
  nav.classList.toggle('active');
});
Typing Text Effect (About Page):
Animates paragraphs sequentially for engaging user experience

7. Deployment

Hosting:
Can be hosted using GitHub Pages, Netlify, or Vercel
Steps to Deploy:
Upload all files to the server or repository
Ensure css/style.css and js/main.js paths are correct
Test navigation links and form functionality

